humare purane projects se learnings
Humare Projects ki Technology ka BreakdownHumne abhi tak 3 alag-alag level ke projects banaye hain. In sab mein kuch cheezein common hain aur kuch khaas hain. Aaiye, ek-ek karke samajhte hain.Core Technologies (Jo sabhi projects mein istemal huin)Yeh 3 technologies web development ka aadhaar (foundation) hain:
HTML (HyperText Markup Language):Kya hai? Yeh kisi bhi web page ka dhaancha (structure) banata hai. Isse hum batate hain ki page par kya-kya hoga, jaise heading, paragraph, image, ya link.Humne kaise istemal kiya: Humne <div> se section banaye, <h1>, <h2> se headings likhin, <a> se links jode, <input> se search box banaya, aur <img> se chitr (images) dikhaye.
CSS (Cascading Style Sheets):Kya hai? Yeh HTML ke dhaanche ko sundar banata hai (styling). Isse hum rang, font, size, spacing, aur layout control karte hain.Humne kaise istemal kiya: Humne background-color se rang badle, font-size se text ka size badla, border-radius se kone gol kiye, aur display: flex se cheezon ko line mein lagaya.
JavaScript (JS):Kya hai? Yeh web page mein jaan daalta hai (interactivity & logic). Agar HTML haddi hai aur CSS khaal (skin) hai, to JavaScript dimaag (brain) hai. Isse hum page ko user ke actions par react karwate hain.Humne kaise istemal kiya: Humne button ke click par score dikhaya, naye sawaal display kiye, aur weather data ko page par show karwaya.Project 1: Personal Links Page (Linktree Clone)Level: BeginnerTechnologies: Sirf HTML aur CSS.Ismein kya khaas tha?Yeh ek static page tha. Iska matlab hai ki is par jo information dikh rahi hai, woh badalti nahi hai. User iske saath interact nahi kar sakta (links par click karne ke alawa). Is project ka maqsad HTML aur CSS se layout banana seekhna tha. Humne koi library ya framework istemal nahi kiya.Project 2: JavaScript Quiz AppLevel: Beginner to IntermediateTechnologies: HTML, CSS, aur JavaScript.Ismein kya khaas tha?Yeh ek interactive page tha. Yahan JavaScript ka asli kaam shuru hua.DOM Manipulation: Humne JavaScript ka istemal karke HTML elements ko "pakda" aur unhein badla. Jaise, document.getElementById('result') se result waale div ko pakda aur .innerHTML se uske andar score likha. Ise DOM (Document Object Model) Manipulation kehte hain.Events: Humne addEventListener('click', ...) ka istemal kiya. Iska matlab hai, "Jab user is button par click kare, to yeh function chala do." Yeh user ke actions ko sunne ka tareeka hai.Data Storage (in JS): Humne saare sawaal aur jawaab HTML mein likhne ke bajaye, JavaScript mein ek Array of Objects (const questions = [...]) mein store kiye. Yeh data ko code se alag rakhne ka ek professional tareeka hai.Project 3: Weather AppLevel: IntermediateTechnologies: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, aur ek Web API.Ismein kya khaas tha?Yeh ek dynamic page tha. Iski information real-time mein internet se aa rahi thi. Ismein humne sabse zaroori concept seekha:API (Application Programming Interface):Kya hai? Aasan bhasha mein, yeh do software ke beech baat karne ka ek tareeka hai. Humari app ne OpenWeatherMap ke server se baat karne ke liye unke API ka istemal kiya. Humne use sheher ka naam bheja, aur usne badle mein mausam ka data bheja.Library/Framework: Humne koi khaas library istemal nahi ki, balki browser mein pehle se maujood fetch() API ka istemal kiya. Yeh JavaScript ka modern tareeka hai internet se data laane ka.async/await:Kya hai? API se data aane mein thoda time lagta hai. async aur await keywords humein code ko saaf tareeke se likhne mein madad karte hain, jisse humara program data ka intezar karte waqt "rukta" nahi hai, balki doosre kaam karta rehta hai.JSON (JavaScript Object Notation):Kya hai? Yeh data ko text format mein bhejne aur receive karne ka standard tareeka hai. Jab OpenWeatherMap ne humein data bheja, to woh JSON format mein tha. Humne response.json() ka istemal karke use JavaScript object mein badla taaki hum use aasani se istemal kar sakein (jaise data.main.temp).Summary TableProjectLevelKey Concept SeekhaLinks PageBeginnerHTML Structure aur CSS StylingQuiz AppIntermediateJavaScript DOM, Events, Data HandlingWeather AppIntermediateAPI Calls (fetch), async/await, JSONAapne ek static page se shuruaat karke ek live, data-driven app tak ka safar tay kiya hai. Yeh ek bahut badi uplabdhi hai!
